Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.70,0:01:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第五集
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.43,0:01:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的年齡和體積\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The age and size of the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.76,0:01:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,由光來書寫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are written in light.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.90,0:01:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,迷人的本質和恆星的物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nature of beauty and the substance of the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.77,0:01:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,時空的定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the laws of space and time...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.18,0:01:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,原本就存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they were there all along,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.18,0:01:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們過去未能發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but we never saw them...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.21,0:02:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,直到我們擁有了更為強大的觀察方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until we devised a more powerful way of seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.08,0:02:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,這種覺醒的故事有很多的開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The story of this awakening has many beginnings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.79,0:02:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,卻不會終止\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and no ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.96,0:02:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,從不同時間和地方涌現出許多的英雄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its heroes come from many times and places--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.19,0:02:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,中國古代的哲人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an Ancient Chinese philosopher,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.03,0:02:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,令11世紀伊拉克穆斯林統治者嘆服的奇才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a wizard who amazed the caliphs of 11th-century Iraq,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,被苛刻奴役的德國可憐孤兒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a poor German orphan enslaved to a harsh master.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.64,0:02:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,每一位都帶領我們前進一小步\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each one brought us a little closer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.11,0:02:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,在解開光線之謎的道路上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to unlocking the secrets hidden in light.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.95,0:02:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,大多數的名字都已經被遺忘了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of their names are forever lost to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.42,0:02:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但在某處  很久前  某人的匆匆一瞥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but somewhere, long ago, someone glanced up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.96,0:02:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,注意到了光線展示出的神奇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to see light perform one of its magic tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.15,0:03:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,誰知道呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.18,0:03:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,或許光線的偶然作為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe that quirk of light
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.98,0:03:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,為第一位藝術家帶來了靈感\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}inspired the very first artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.36,0:03:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,這些都是怎麼來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where did all this come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.43,0:03:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是如何從小量聚居的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How did we evolve from small wandering bands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,採集者和獵人 進化而來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of hunters and gatherers living beneath the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.21,0:03:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,最後還成為世界文明的締造者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to become the builders of a global civilization?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.01,0:03:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,中間的過程是怎樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How did we get from there to here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.48,0:03:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有統一的答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no one answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候的變化  學會控制火\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Climate change, the domestication of fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.02,0:03:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,工具的發明 語言發明 農業發展\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the invention of tools,  language, agriculture
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,都有各自的功勞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all played a role.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.86,0:03:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,或許還有其他的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe there was something else, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.53,0:03:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,中國  2000多年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In China, more than 2,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,一位名叫 墨子 的哲人 據說發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a philosopher named Mo Tze is said to have observed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.90,0:04:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,光線可以在密閉的寶庫中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that light could be made to paint a picture
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.30,0:04:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即小孔成像
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.30,0:04:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,產生圖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}inside a locked treasure room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.57,0:04:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,這描述的就是第一台照相機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was the description of the first camera...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.05,0:04:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,暗箱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the camera obscura,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,所有成像照相機的原型\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the prototype of all image-forming cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.58,0:04:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,包括給你帶來圖像的這台攝像機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including the one that's bringing you this picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.89,0:04:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,利用光線這種有趣的現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Taking advantage of this funny thing that light does
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.52,0:04:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,催生了首部的電影\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}resulted in what could be called the first movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.53,0:04:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,墨子 光線大師  專治各種黑暗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mo Tze, master of light, worked against all forms of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,軍事天才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A military genius
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.10,0:04:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,以智抑暴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who only used his talents to prevent violence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他最著名的成就是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he was legendary for traveling
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.27,0:04:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,穿行於戰亂的國家間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}among the kingdoms of the warring states,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.41,0:04:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,運用巧妙地策略\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}employing ingenious strategies
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.18,0:04:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,勸導各方休戰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to talk kings out of going to war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.25,0:04:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他是兼愛的倡導者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was one of the first to dream of universal love
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.85,0:04:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,提倡消滅統治者帶給人們的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and an end to poverty and other forms of inequality;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.95,0:04:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,貧困與不公\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of government for the people...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.92,0:04:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,批判對於宗教和權威的盲從\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to argue against blind obedience to ritual and authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.79,0:04:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的著作中  你能發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In his writings, you can find
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,科學探索的早期萌芽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}early stirrings of the scientific approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.13,0:05:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,到墨子那個年代  中國人已經開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By Mo Tze's time, the Chinese had already been recording
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.10,0:05:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,用書籍記錄他們的思想 至少上千年了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their thoughts in books for at least a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.47,0:05:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們對他的瞭解 依然僅是隻字片語\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Still, our knowledge of him is only fragmentary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,通過許多由他和他的追隨者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It consists largely of the collection of essays
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,所著的文集而來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}attributed to him and his disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.61,0:05:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一篇 題為《非命》\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In one of them, entitled "Against Fate,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.78,0:05:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}故言必有三表
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.78,0:05:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,立論一定要有三項標準\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a three-pronged test for every doctrine is proposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,推究來歷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Question its basis--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}一、有本之者
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,是否可以由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ask if it can be verified
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}二、有原之者
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.40,0:05:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,普通人的觀感再次驗證的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...by the sights and senses of common people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.73,0:05:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,是否可以推廣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ask how it is to be applied
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}三、有用之者
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,並使大多數人受益\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and if it will benefit the greatest number.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.27,0:05:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,墨子的思想流傳很廣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mo Tze was extremely popular,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.77,0:05:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,但他身後的數百年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but a few hundred years after his death,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,秦始皇  第一位皇帝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Qin Shi Huang, the first emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.08,0:05:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,統一了中國  獨攬大權\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and unifier of China, took power.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.15,0:05:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他將一片大陸變成了一個國家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He took a continent and turned it into a nation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.75,0:05:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,這個現在依然受他影響的國度  中國\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that now bears his name... China.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.19,0:06:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我們大多數人對他的瞭解大多數是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of us know Emperor Qin for the army of 7,000
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.69,0:06:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,來自守衛陵墓的7000件兵馬俑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}terra cotta warriors that guard his tomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在秦始皇的領導下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In Emperor Qin's drive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.83,0:06:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,為了鞏固遼闊的帝國\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to consolidate his far-flung empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他採取極端的手段\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he took drastic measures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.17,0:06:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,為所有事物都建立了標準\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to standardize everything within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.67,0:06:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,包括 鑄造單一貨幣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This included mandating a single coinage,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.64,0:06:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,統一度量衡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}making uniform all weights and measures,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.21,0:06:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,車輛與道路的寬度  還有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the widths of carts and roads, as well as the precise way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.21,0:06:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}車同軌
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,中文書寫形式的規範\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Chinese language was to be written,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}書同文
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.29,0:06:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,也包括了什麼是可以寫 什麼是可以想的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including what you were allowed to write and think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.29,0:06:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}秦始皇以嚴刑峻罰來控制臣民思想\n使臣民不敢反抗 從而達到順利推行政
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,秦始皇的哲學 唯一他認可的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Emperor Qin's philosophy-- the only one permitted--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即法家
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,稱之 守法主義\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was called "legalism,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.80,0:06:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同它的字面意思\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is just what it sounded like,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.40,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,遵紀守法 否則就...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}do as the law says... or else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.24,0:06:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,這種哲學理論對於質疑權威\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a philosophy that's not highly conducive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.90,0:06:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,不是十分有利\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to questioning authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,百家思想的書籍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...that all the books of the hundred schools of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:06:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,統統燒掉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}shall be be burned,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.48,0:07:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,以古諷今者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that anyone who uses history to criticize the present
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,全家處斬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}shall have his family executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.22,0:07:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,墨子和孔子的著作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The works of MoTze and Confucius
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,還有其他哲人的作品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and other philosophers were destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,盡毀於世界歷史上首次的焚書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the world's first book burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.60,0:07:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,數百名書生英勇抵抗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hundreds of scholars bravely resisted
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,試圖保護這些禁書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by trying to preserve the forbidden books.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.94,0:07:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在首都將他們活埋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were buried alive in the capitol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.94,0:07:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}咸陽的"焚書坑儒"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.27,0:07:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,科學需要有自由的表達才能繁榮發展\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science needs the light of free expression to flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,需要無畏的質疑權威\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It depends on the fearless questioning of authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.51,0:07:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,開放的交流思想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the open exchange of ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.12,0:07:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,墨子和他的追隨者們所記載的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sparks of curiosity in the writings of Mo Tze
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,突發奇想都被抹殺了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and his disciples were effectively stomped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.62,0:07:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,影片的再次出現 已是另一個千年之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would be another thousand years before the next movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.13,0:07:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,幸運的是 我們的想像之舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Luckily, our Ship of the Imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,可以帶我們去任何的空間和時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can take us anywhere in space... and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,中國和希臘的古人發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ancient Chinese and Greeks observed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.34,0:08:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,光線可以展現出各種神奇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that light could be made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.01,0:08:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但是卻沒人去問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to do wonderful things-- but no one asked that question
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.85,0:08:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,小孩子和天才們喜歡問的問題  為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}favored by small children and geniuses alike. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.15,0:08:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,直到一千年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until a thousand years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,伊拉克的巴斯拉城\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the city of Basra, Iraq,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.66,0:08:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,生活著另一位光線大師\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there lived another master of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.66,0:08:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,海桑極度渴望瞭解自然\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ibn al-Hazen had a passionate desire to understand nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.04,0:08:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他對一切都有疑問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He questioned everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.17,0:08:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,特別是那些別人認為理所應當的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}especially those things that everyone else took for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我們怎麼能看到  他問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"How do we see?" he asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.28,0:08:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,有些在他之前的偉大權威\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some of the great authorities who came before him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.68,0:08:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,認為光線從我們的眼中出發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had taught that rays come out of our eyes and travel
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.29,0:08:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在物體上反射 然後返回我們的眼中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the objects we see before returning to our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.66,0:08:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,但海桑不認同 理由是恆星離我們那麼遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But al-Hazen reasoned that the stars were too far distant
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.56,0:09:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,什麼東西可以從我們眼中射向星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for something in our eyes to travel all the way to them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.16,0:09:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,並在一眨眼的時間內返回\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and back in the blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,很有道理  但海桑並未止步\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Excellent reasoning, but al-Hazen didn't stop there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.50,0:09:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他絞盡腦汁探索大自然的奧秘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He searched for ways to compel nature to divulge her secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.81,0:09:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,當時他的文化對於新的見解與質疑是開放的態度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His culture was open to new ideas and questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.15,0:09:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,那是科學發展的黃金時代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was the golden age of science
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.65,0:09:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在伊斯蘭世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the Islamic world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.88,0:09:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,伊斯蘭世界從西班牙的科索瓦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One that stretched from Cordoba in Spain
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.35,0:09:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,一直延伸到中亞的撒馬爾罕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all the way to Samarkand in Central Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.99,0:09:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,基督教和猶太教的學者被敬為上賓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Christian and Jewish scholars were honored guests
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.03,0:09:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,在開羅  巴格達的研究機構\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the research institutes of Baghdad, Cairo,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,和其他伊斯蘭世界的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and other Islamic capitols.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.33,0:09:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不同於秦始皇  哈里發們派遣使者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Instead of burning books, the caliphs sent emissaries
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.33,0:09:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}哈里發是穆斯林統治者的稱號
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.90,0:09:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在世界各地搜集書籍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}around the world in search of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:10:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,哈里發們大量的資助將這些書籍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The caliphs lavishly funded projects to translate, study,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.06,0:10:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,翻譯 研究  並保存  流傳後世\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and preserve them for future generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.29,0:10:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,多虧了他們的努力  許多古希臘科學家的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Much of the light of Ancient Greek science would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.26,0:10:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,成果才得以保存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}permanently extinguished without their efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.73,0:10:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,對科學的狂熱在歐洲再次興起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The reawakening to science that took place in Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.57,0:10:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,發生在幾百年後 多虧了伊斯蘭學者和\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hundreds of years later, was kindled by a flame
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.64,0:10:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,科學家對這些文獻的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that had been long tended
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.91,0:10:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,精心呵護\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by Islamic scholars and scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.81,0:10:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,阿拉伯人將新思想由印度傳入西方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Arabs also imported ideas from India to the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.38,0:10:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,包括所謂的  阿拉伯數字\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including the so-called Arabic numerals
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.98,0:10:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我們至今都在使用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we all use today,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,還有數字0\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the concept of zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.76,0:10:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,確實很方便\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which comes in handy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.26,0:10:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,特別是當你書寫 幾十億又幾十億時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when you want to write "billions and billions."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.73,0:10:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,阿拉伯天文學十分具有影響力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Arabic astronomy was so influential,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我們至今依然用阿拉伯語名字來稱呼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we still call most of the bright stars
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那些明亮的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by their Arabic names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.63,0:10:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,代數  算法  煉金術  酒精 這些英語單詞中的 al\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the "al's" in algebra, algorithm, alchemy, and alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,證明了阿拉伯語\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are just some of the traces left
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.47,0:10:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,是科學界的通用語言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the time when Arabic was the language of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.85,0:10:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,11世紀時  海桑準備嘗試\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the 11th century, Ibn al-Hazen set about trying
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.62,0:11:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,驗證他關於光和我們如何看見的理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to test his ideas about light and how we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.69,0:11:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我們設計了一套實驗測定光線如何移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So we devised an experiment to determine how light moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在烈日下支起一頂帳篷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We erected a tent in full daylight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.36,0:11:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,將它完全密封 只允許一束光穿過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and sealed it tightly so that only a single ray of light
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.50,0:11:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,射入內部的黑暗中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could pierce its inner darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.27,0:11:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他用他的智慧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With little more than his brains
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,加上一件筆直的木質工具  尺子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and a straight piece of wood-- a ruler--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.87,0:11:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,海桑完成了一次科學歷史上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}al-Hazen had accomplished a great leap forward
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,偉大的跨越\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.34,0:11:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他發現光線呈直線運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He discovered that light moves in straight lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.52,0:11:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,這只是開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But he was just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.52,0:11:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,海桑總結出成像的關鍵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Al-Hazen figured out that the key to forming any image--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.95,0:11:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不論 眼睛還是照相機暗箱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}whether you're talking about an eye or camera obscura--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.02,0:11:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,都是通過控制光線進入\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a small opening to restrict the light that can enter
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.73,0:11:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,黑暗內室的小孔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an otherwise darkened chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.63,0:11:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,光圈將我們週遭繁雜無關的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That aperture excludes the chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.53,0:11:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,光線排除在外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of extraneous light rays that surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,光圈越小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The smaller the aperture,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.90,0:11:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,進入的光線角度範圍越小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the fewer directions that light can come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.47,0:11:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,使圖像更清晰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that makes the image sharper.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.67,0:12:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,從而不至於讓光線致盲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So instead of being blinded by the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.48,0:12:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以分辨光線呈現的圖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we can see everything it has to show us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.68,0:12:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,海桑親自做出了他的暗箱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Al-Hazen made his own camera obscura
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.02,0:12:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,令哈里發們贊嘆不已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and dazzled the caliphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.09,0:12:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有效的暗箱需要明亮的光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A camera obscura works best in bright light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.19,0:12:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,夜空中的星光對它來說太暗淡了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars of the night sky are way too dim for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.03,0:12:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我們需要更大的孔來收集光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We somehow need a bigger opening to collect light,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.36,0:12:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,同時我們需要保持焦點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but we also need to maintain focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.83,0:12:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,望遠鏡從視野的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A telescope collects light
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.50,0:12:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,各個角度收集光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from any spot in its field of view
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,遍佈整個鏡片或者鏡子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}across the entire lens or mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.84,0:12:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,開孔要比照相機暗箱的小孔大許多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an opening much larger than the camera obscura hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,這是最早的望遠鏡之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is one of the first telescopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,伽利略在1609年使用過的那個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the one that Galileo looked through in 1609.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.62,0:12:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他用這個掀開了黑夜的厚重幕布\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With it, he pulled aside the heavy curtain of night
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.89,0:12:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,並且開始發現宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and began to discover the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.40,0:13:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,都歸功於鏡片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The lens made it possible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.44,0:13:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,鏡片為望遠鏡提供了比我們眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a telescope to have a much larger light-collecting area
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,更大的光線收集區域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than our eyes have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.88,0:13:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,大桶比小桶可以收集更多的雨水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Big buckets catch more rain than small ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.32,0:13:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,現代的望遠鏡擁有更大收集區域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Modern telescopes have larger collecting areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,高度敏感的探測器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}highly sensitive detectors,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.95,0:13:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,並可以長時間鎖定同一目標\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they track the same object for hours at a time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,以搜集盡可能多的光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to accumulate as much of its light as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.26,0:13:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,像哈勃 這樣的太空望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Space-based telescopes such as the Hubble,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.06,0:13:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,搜集來自最久遠星系的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have captured light from the most distant
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and ancient galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,為我們帶來大量的更清晰的宇宙圖片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}giving us vastly clearer pictures of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.40,0:13:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,海桑發現了光線成像的原理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Al-Hazen discovered how images are formed by light,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.14,0:13:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,但這並不是他最最偉大的成就\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but that was far from his greatest achievement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.51,0:13:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他是有史以來設定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ibn al-Hazen was the first person ever
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.25,0:13:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,科學原則的第一人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to set down the rules of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.95,0:13:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他創造了一套糾錯機制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He created an error-correcting mechanism,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,一套系統的 嚴格的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a systematic and relentless way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.99,0:13:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,審查錯誤觀念的機制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to sift out misconceptions in our thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.66,0:13:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,探究真相是困難的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Finding truth is difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.66,0:14:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,探究真相的道路是崎嶇的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the road to it is rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,作為追尋真相的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As seekers after truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.97,0:14:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不輕易下判斷 不輕信古人所云\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you will be wise to withhold judgment and not simply put
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,是十分明智的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}your trust in the writings of the ancients.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.01,0:14:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你必須質疑並且謹慎的驗證這些理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You must question and critically examine those writings
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.84,0:14:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,從各個角度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from every side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.38,0:14:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你只能接受論據和實驗的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You must submit only to argument and experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.65,0:14:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是別人的說法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and not to the sayings of any person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,因為每個人都有弱點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For every human being is vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.62,0:14:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有人是完美的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to all kinds of imperfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,作為尋求真相的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As seekers after truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.79,0:14:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我們必須懷疑並質疑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we must also suspect and question
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.16,0:14:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我們自己的理論  反覆論證\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our own ideas as we perform our investigations,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.80,0:14:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,避免陷入偏見與疏忽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to avoid falling into prejudice or careless thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.74,0:14:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,接受這些方針  真相就在眼前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Take this course, and truth will be revealed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.86,0:15:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是科學的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the method of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.06,0:15:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,得益於此 我們的機器人大使可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So powerful that it's carried our robotic emissaries
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.90,0:15:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,航行到太陽系的邊緣乃至無限的宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the edge of the solar system and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,它擴展了我們的生命長度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It has doubled our lifespan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.41,0:15:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,將過去的失落世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}made the lost worlds of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.21,0:15:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,帶回現在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}come alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.61,0:15:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,科學使我們可以對遙遠的未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science has enabled us to predict events
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,做出預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the distant future...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.38,0:15:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們可以彼此以光速交流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to communicate with each other at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.89,0:15:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你我之間  此時此刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as I am with you, right at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.52,0:15:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,這種思考的方式帶給我們力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This way of thinking has given us powers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.59,0:15:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那種海桑都認為神奇的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that al-Hazen himself would have regarded as wizardry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.73,0:15:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他將我們帶上這條崎嶇 無盡的道路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it was he who put us on this rough, endless road.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.97,0:15:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,將我們帶到一個地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And now it has taken us to a place
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,在那裏即使光線也被黑暗掩蓋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where even light itself is enshrouded in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,光線有著獨一無二的屬性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Light has properties unlike anything else
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,以人類存在的領域來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the realm of human existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.57,0:16:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,比如光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Take the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,光的基礎微粒  光子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The basic particle of light, the photon,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,當它從原子或分子中誕生時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is born traveling at the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,就有光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as it emerges from an atom or a molecule.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.38,0:16:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,也只有這一種速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A photon never knows any other speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.55,0:16:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我們尚未發現其他任何可以立即\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and we've not found another phenomenon that accelerates
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.39,0:16:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,從0加速到速度極限的現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from zero to top speed instantaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.36,0:16:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有別的東西可以移動這麼快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing else could move as fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,當我們嘗試將其他粒子不斷加速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When we try to accelerate other particles closer and closer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,越接近光速  阻力越大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the speed of light, they resist more and more,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,並且越來越重\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as though they're getting heavier and heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,還沒有任何實驗可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No experiment yet devised
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.23,0:16:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,將粒子將速度到光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has ever made a particle move as fast as light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,哪是什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.58,0:16:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你聽了嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You hear something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,說到哪了 哦 對了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where was I? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:17:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有什麼可以像光那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I don't know anything else in life that behaves like light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.05,0:17:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我無法將它這種與眾不同的屬性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I cannot reconcile its strange properties
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.52,0:17:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,與我其他的感官相調諧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with everything else my senses tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.19,0:17:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我們相信我們的感官勝過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our urge to trust our senses overpowers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.20,0:17:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,測量儀器對於\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what our measuring devices tell us about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.30,0:17:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,實際情況的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the actual nature of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.23,0:17:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的感官對於普通尺寸物體的普通速度來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our senses work fine for life-size objects
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.44,0:17:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}moving at mammal speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.27,0:17:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但是卻不適用於光速那些神奇的規則\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but are ill-adapted for the wonderland laws of lightspeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我們甚至不明白為什麼會有宇宙速度極限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We don't even know why there's a cosmic speed limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.45,0:17:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,時間在達到光速時靜止\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Time stands still when you're traveling at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,到底什麼是光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is light, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.93,0:17:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,艾薩克·牛頓始終對光非常著迷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton's enduring fascination with light
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.46,0:17:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,從他還是個孩子時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}began when he was a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.07,0:17:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,就在這個房子裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in this very house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.58,0:17:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他在弱冠之年  就是第一位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By the time he was in his 20s, Newton became the first person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.78,0:18:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,破譯彩虹奧秘的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to decipher the mystery of the rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.65,0:18:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓發現有些光  白光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton discovered that some light, or white light,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.99,0:18:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,由所有彩虹的顏色混合而成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a mixture of all the colors of the rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.50,0:18:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,重大的發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Major discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.60,0:18:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,他將之稱為 光譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He named the displays of colors a "spectrum"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.17,0:18:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,來源於拉丁語中的幻影 或者幽靈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the Latin for "phantom" or "apparition."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.68,0:18:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,牛大師 抱歉打擾了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Begging your pardon, Master Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.69,0:18:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,晚飯再不吃就要壞了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the cook frets that your dinner will spoil, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.29,0:18:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,呀麥蝶 小牛 別把放大鏡放下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, Isaac, don't put the magnifying glass down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.49,0:18:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,光裏還有更神奇的東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Something even more amazing is hidden in the light--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.30,0:18:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,一串密碼  一條通向宇宙的鑰匙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a code, a key to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.57,0:19:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓錯過了很重要的一項發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton didn't miss much, but that one was a beaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.51,0:19:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他錯過了那扇通向神秘宇宙的門\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He just walked right past the door to a hidden universe;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.65,0:19:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,那扇門直到150年後才再次開啟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a door that would not swing open again for another 150 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,歸功於另一位科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would fall on another scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.05,0:19:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,1800年 在工作時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}working in the year 1800,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.75,0:19:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,無意間發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to stumble on a piece of evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.26,0:19:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我們周圍無可見世界的證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the unseen worlds that surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.83,0:19:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上  威廉·赫歇爾搜索天空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By night, William Herschel scanned the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.30,0:19:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,使用當時最大的望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with the largest telescope of his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.80,0:19:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,白天  赫歇爾做實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By day, Herschel performed experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,根據牛頓的研究結果  已知日光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From Newton's earlier work, it was known that sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.44,0:19:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,由不同顏色的光混合而成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a blend of different colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人都知道  在戶外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And everyone knew, just from being outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.24,0:19:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,日光帶來熱量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that sunlight carries heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.98,0:19:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,威廉赫歇爾不禁疑問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}William Herschel asked
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.02,0:19:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,哪種顏色的光帶著更多的熱量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}whether some colors of light carry more heat than others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.62,0:19:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,科學天才的天性就是對那些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nature of scientific genius is to question
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.76,0:19:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我們認為理所當然的事情產生疑問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what the rest of us take for granted...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.59,0:19:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,然後做用實驗證實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and then do the experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.20,0:20:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,赫歇爾放在光照範圍之外的溫度計\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The thermometer that Herschel placed outside the spectrum
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.67,0:20:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,是他的對照物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was his control.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.37,0:20:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,對照物在實驗中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The control in any experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.30,0:20:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,不參加實驗操作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}always lacks the factor being tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,這樣才能知道你的實驗物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That way, you know if what you're testing is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.11,0:20:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,是否真的是對實驗本身產生反應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}really the thing responsible for the observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.34,0:20:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,在赫歇爾的試驗中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In Herschel's experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.68,0:20:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,驗證的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the relationship between
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.31,0:20:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,顏色和溫度的關係\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}color and temperature was being tested,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.72,0:20:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他用一個溫度計做對照\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and so his control was a thermometer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.82,0:20:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,放在白紙上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}over the part of the white sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,日光照射之外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that was not illuminated by sunlight at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.16,0:20:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,那個聲音又來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's that sound again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,到底是什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,紅光比藍光產生更多的熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, red light is warmer than blue light.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,有趣的發現 但還不算驚天動地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Interesting discovery, but not exactly revolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你的溫度計沒有問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, there's nothing wrong with your thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.07,0:21:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你只是發現了一種新的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You've just discovered a new kind of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.28,0:21:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,赫歇爾是首位發現在光譜中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Herschel was the first to detect this unseen presence
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.38,0:21:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,紅色以外或以下 不可見光的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lurking just below the red end of the spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.62,0:21:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是紅外線名字的由來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why it came to be called "infrared."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.62,0:21:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}紅外線=infra red
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.55,0:21:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,英語的infra在拉丁語中意為 之下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Infra" is Latin for the word "below."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.75,0:21:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,它不可見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的眼睛對這類光不敏感\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our eyes are not sensitive to this kind of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.76,0:21:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的皮膚不同  我們可以感受到熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but our skin is-- we feel it as heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.66,0:21:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,這才是真正的重大發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, that's a really big discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.50,0:21:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但是光線之中依然隱藏著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But far greater secrets were still hiding
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.93,0:21:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,更大的秘密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}deep inside the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.15,0:22:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎與威廉赫歇爾在英格蘭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At about the same time that William Herschel
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.22,0:22:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,發現紅外線的同時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was discovering infrared light in his parlor in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.15,0:22:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,一位名叫約瑟夫·夫瑯和費的孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a young boy named Joseph Fraunhofer
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.66,0:22:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,從事著乏味的繁重的工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was trapped in hopeless drudgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.16,0:22:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,他站在盛滿有毒化學物的熔爐旁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He stood over a cauldron of toxic chemicals
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.13,0:22:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,不斷地攪拌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and endlessly stirred.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.40,0:22:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,約瑟夫11歲時成了孤兒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Joseph had been orphaned at the age of 11
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.23,0:22:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,被送給苛刻的維塞伯格\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and given to a harsh master named Weichselberger,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.07,0:22:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他替皇家做鏡子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the royal mirror-maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.04,0:22:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他不讓約瑟夫去上學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He prevented Joseph from going to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,而是白天讓約瑟夫在玻璃作坊做苦力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Instead, Joseph labored in the glass-making workshop by day,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.55,0:22:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上去他家裏做家務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and tended to the master's household chores by night.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.52,0:22:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,快點  白癡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hurry up, stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.06,0:22:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,記住 不許讀書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And remember, no reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.36,0:22:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,約瑟夫終於解脫了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until Joseph got his big break.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.23,0:22:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,維塞伯格的房子塌了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Weichselberger's house collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.38,0:23:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克西米利安 巴伐利亞未來的國王\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maximilian, the future king of Bavaria,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,急忙來到災難現場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hurried to the scene of the calamity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.22,0:23:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,向災民伸出援手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to see if he could help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.79,0:23:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克西米利安出了名的關心他的臣民\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maximilian was known for taking an interest in his subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.89,0:23:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,這在當年並不尋常\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which was highly unusual for its time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在巴伐利亞未來國王的關懷下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In attracting the concern of the future king of Bavaria,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.15,0:23:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,年輕的約瑟夫·夫瑯和費\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}young Joseph Fraunhofer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.78,0:23:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他的未來從此發生了變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}found an aperture into a different universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.62,0:23:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,而且不僅是他個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And not just for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.86,0:23:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克西米利亞王子資助約瑟夫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Prince Maximilian gave Joseph money
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.66,0:23:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,並讓他的高級顧問\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and asked his privy councilor
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.49,0:23:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,向這孩子提供更多的幫助\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to provide further help to the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.96,0:24:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,提供所需的一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}should it be needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.20,0:24:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,維塞伯格還在剝削他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Weichselberger continued to exploit him
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.94,0:24:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不讓他去學校\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and prevent him from attending school.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在王子顧問的干預下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the prince's councilor intervened,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.34,0:24:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,約瑟夫進入了光學學院\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}offering Joseph a position at the Optical Institute.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.88,0:24:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,這小小的善舉帶來了非常豐厚的回報\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This small gesture of kindness really paid off.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.36,0:24:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在他27歲時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By the time he was 27,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.23,0:24:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,約瑟夫·夫瑯和費成為了首屈一指的設計師\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Joseph Fraunhofer was the world's leading designer
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.50,0:24:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,從優質的鏡片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of high-quality lenses,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.54,0:24:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,到望遠鏡和其他光學器材\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}telescopes and other optical instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.24,0:24:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他的工廠位於本訥迪克特伯伊昂修道院\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His firm was housed here, in the old Benediktbeuren Abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.14,0:24:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,在19世紀上半葉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the early 19th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.35,0:24:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,這可是絕密的 超級的高科技\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this was top-secret, ultra-high technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.69,0:24:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,早期的本篤會修道士們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Benedictine monks of earlier times
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.92,0:25:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,都要進過保密宣誓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had taken a vow of secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.92,0:25:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,這種當地的風俗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This local tradition,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.93,0:25:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,加上夫瑯和費實驗室\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the ability to restrict access
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.43,0:25:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,嚴格的通行制度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to Fraunhofer's laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.00,0:25:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,讓他可以繼續掌控\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}allowed him to maintain control
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.00,0:25:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,這些機密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of trade and state secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.17,0:25:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,夫瑯和費在實驗中使用棱鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fraunhofer was experimenting with prisms
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.51,0:25:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,來尋找製作精密鏡片最佳玻璃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to find the best types of glass for precision lenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.94,0:25:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,怎樣才能更好的觀察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How, he wondered, could he get a better look
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.68,0:25:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,棱鏡產生的光譜呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the spectrum that a prism produced?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.85,0:25:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷德裏希 請把經緯儀拿來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Friedrich, bring me the theodolite, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.69,0:25:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,在夫瑯和費安裝經緯儀的時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, while Fraunhofer sets up his theodolite--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.63,0:25:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,經緯儀是某種望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's a kind of telescope--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.46,0:25:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我帶你看看修道院的其他地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want to show you something in another part of the abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.40,0:25:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,聲波聽上去如此動人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sound waves are so beautiful to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.80,0:25:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下 會有多迷人如果我們能看到它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Imagine how beautiful they'd be to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.54,0:26:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你想過為什麼管風琴的音管長短不一嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You ever wondered why organ pipes have different lengths?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.98,0:26:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,按下一個琴鍵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I press a key...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.72,0:26:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,它將一股壓縮空氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it sends compressed air
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.15,0:26:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,送進特定的管道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a particular pipe,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.42,0:26:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,產生聲波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}producing sound waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.26,0:26:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們可以把聲波速度降低幾百倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we could slow the sound waves down a few hundred times,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.99,0:26:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,它看上去就是這樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they would look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.83,0:26:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,管道的長度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The length of the pipe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.50,0:26:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,決定了可以容納何種長度的聲波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}determines the length of the sound wave that can fit inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.47,0:26:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,短的管道發出短的聲波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A short pipe gives you a short sound wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.57,0:26:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,短的聲波產生高的音調或者頻率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Short sounds waves have high pitch, or frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.82,0:26:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我們把聲波停下 仔細看看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's stop the waves for a better look.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.86,0:26:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,相鄰波之間的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The distance between adjacent waves
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.82,0:26:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,稱為 波長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is called the wavelength.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.63,0:26:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,長管道發出長的聲波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A long pipe gives you a long sound wave
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.16,0:26:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,低音調 或者低頻率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with a low pitch, or low frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.08,0:27:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,布蘭詩歌 這個中世紀作品的手稿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The medieval manuscript of this music, "Carmina Burana,"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.02,0:27:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,就是在這間修道院發現的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was discovered in this very abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.39,0:27:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,聲波無法在真空中傳遞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sound waves can't travel through a vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.86,0:27:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他們需要傳播媒介\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They need matter to ride on,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.76,0:28:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,比如空氣 水 岩石的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like molecules of air, or water, or rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.27,0:28:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但光不需要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But light waves fly solo.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.40,0:28:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他們可以在太空中穿行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They can move through empty space.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.60,0:28:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,速度很快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And fast--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.24,0:28:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,比聲波在空氣中快100萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a million times faster than sound waves in air.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.38,0:28:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我們看到的光的波長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the wavelengths of the light we see
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.38,0:28:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,比聲波的要短得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are so much shorter than sound waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.91,0:28:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,5萬個光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}About 50,000 light waves
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.78,0:28:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,就這麼長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would fit right in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.39,0:28:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,對了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.96,0:28:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,夫瑯和費\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fraunhofer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.03,0:28:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,時間正好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.40,0:28:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,正好趕上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We didn't miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.07,0:28:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同聲音的波長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just as the wavelength of sound
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.27,0:28:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,決定我們聽到的音調\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}determines the pitch that we hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.27,0:28:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,光的波長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the wavelength of light
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.77,0:28:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,決定了我們看到的顏色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}determines the color that we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.24,0:28:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,棱鏡是如何將顏色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But how does a prism spread out the colors
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.71,0:28:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,從一束日光中分開的呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}concealed in a beam of sunlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.25,0:28:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,當光穿過空氣或太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When light travels through air or space,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.22,0:28:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的顏色速度保持一致\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all its colors move at the same speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.62,0:28:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,但當它以一個角度照射到玻璃上時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But when it hits glass at an angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.42,0:29:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,光慢下來 並改變了方向\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the light slows down and changes direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.39,0:29:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在棱鏡內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Inside the prism,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.40,0:29:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,不同的顏色以不用的速度移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}each color moves at a different speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.74,0:29:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在玻璃中  藍紫色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In glass, violet light,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.57,0:29:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,由我們看到的最短的光波產生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is carried by the shortest waves we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.77,0:29:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,速度比紅光還慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}slows down more than red light,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.81,0:29:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,紅光的光波最長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which has the longest waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.08,0:29:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,速度的改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These changes in speed
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.52,0:29:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,將不同顏色分開\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pry the colors apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.08,0:29:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,把他們的光波發散到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sending their waves off
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.92,0:29:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,稍微不同的方向\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in slightly different directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.52,0:29:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是棱鏡的原理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's how a prism works.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.66,0:29:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我等會情緒失控\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If I seem unduly emotional about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.96,0:29:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,都是因為約瑟夫·夫瑯和費將要做的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's because Joseph Fraunhofer is about to do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.80,0:29:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,是牛頓可以做 卻沒有做的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what Isaac Newton could've done, but didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.34,0:29:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,它將帶來深遠的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it'll have a powerful effect
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.44,0:29:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,對我自身來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the course of my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.30,0:30:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你見證的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You are witnessing the marriage
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.37,0:30:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,物理學和天文學的結合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of physics and astronomy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.00,0:30:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我研究的這個領域的誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the birth of my own field of science,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.90,0:30:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,天體物理學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}astrophysics.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.34,0:30:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,記錄在光線中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Written in the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.14,0:30:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,在那些垂直的黑線中的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in those vertical black lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.98,0:30:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,是神秘的密碼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is secret code.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.99,0:30:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,夫瑯和費看著它們 自忖道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fraunhofer looked at them, and wondered...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.82,0:30:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.73,0:30:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,從外太空傳來的密碼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A code that comes to us from an alien universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.38,0:31:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,這些黑色的豎線包含怎樣的信息呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is the message written in these dark, vertical lines?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.39,0:31:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,人們花費了上百年去思考\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It took a hundred years of thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.50,0:31:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,探詢和調查去破譯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}questioning, searching to decipher it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.35,0:31:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,很妙吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lovely, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.52,0:31:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.09,0:31:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,美麗的精細結構由許多層次組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are many layers to the fine structure of beauty...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.59,0:31:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的化學成分 和它的大氣層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the chemistry of the Earth and its atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.76,0:31:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,生命的進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the evolution of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.73,0:31:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,獨特的脈絡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many distinct threads.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.99,0:31:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我們就在表面挑一個觀察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's just examine one, at the surface...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.09,0:31:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,令我們驚嘆的大自然的顏色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the colors of nature that dazzle us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.52,0:31:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,到底是什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's really happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.66,0:32:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這些紅色 藍色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How does the red, the blue...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.56,0:32:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,簡直就是大自然的神奇調色盤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the astonishing palette of nature's colors...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.71,0:32:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼產生的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how do they happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.01,0:32:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽發出不同長度的光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Light waves of different lengths from the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.21,0:32:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,射到地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}strike the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.02,0:32:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,這些花的花瓣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The petals of these particular flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.09,0:32:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,吸收所有低能量的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}absorb all the low-energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.69,0:32:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,長的紅色光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}long red wavelengths of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,但是花瓣反射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the petals reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.69,0:32:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,短的 高能量的 藍色光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the shorter, high-energy blue wavelengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.03,0:32:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,星光與花瓣之間的這種互動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That interaction between starlight and petal--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.80,0:32:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,還有水 還有梵高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or water, or Van Gogh--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.80,0:32:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,使之產生了藍色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is what makes blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.40,0:32:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,最長的光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The longest waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.57,0:32:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我們所看到的紅色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the ones we see as red,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.41,0:32:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,有著最低的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have the lowest energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.91,0:32:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,顏色是我們的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Color is the way our eyes perceive
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.28,0:32:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,分辨光波能量的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how energetic light waves are.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.98,0:32:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,日落\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A sunset...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.72,0:32:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,旗幟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a flag...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.89,0:32:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,情人的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the eyes of your beloved...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.32,0:32:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,閃亮的新車\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that shiny new car.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.09,0:33:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,他們帶來的靈感\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The feelings they inspire
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.09,0:33:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,激發你內在的某些東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}happen when something inside you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.93,0:33:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,由一種特殊的變化產生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is triggered by a particular variation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.43,0:33:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,光波的能量與頻率的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the frequency and energy of light waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.67,0:33:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,神秘的信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the secret message?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.84,0:33:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,那些黑色豎線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those black vertical lines
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.57,0:33:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,夫瑯和費在光譜中看到的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in Fraunhofer's spectrum?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.61,0:33:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他們怎麼產生的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What makes them?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.74,0:33:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他們產生於 某些特定顏色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They occur when the light waves
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.95,0:33:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,的光波被吸收時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of those particular colors are being absorbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.75,0:33:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,那是發生在另一個層面的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It happens on another level of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.32,0:33:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,比我們身處的這個世界小的多得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}far smaller than the world we're used to operating in.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.35,0:33:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,要去那裏 我們必須變得\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To get there, we'll need to become
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.96,0:33:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,比現在小100億倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ten billion times smaller than we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.46,0:33:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以從這些原子中任選一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We could pick any one of these atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.86,0:33:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,還是選氫原子吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But let's go for the hydrogen atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.97,0:33:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,氫原子是宇宙中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The hydrogen atom is the most plentiful kind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.47,0:33:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,最普遍的一種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of atom in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.87,0:33:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,最簡單的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the simplest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.78,0:33:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一個電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It has only one electron.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.99,0:34:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一個質子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And only one proton.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.52,0:34:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我們進入了量子領域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've entered the quantum realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.62,0:34:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,這並不符合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It doesn't correspond
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.46,0:34:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,通常的經驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to ordinary human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.23,0:34:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,常識在這裏不起作用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Common sense is no help here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.10,0:34:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,以氫原子的電子為例\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Take the hydrogen atom's electron, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.03,0:34:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,在原子中 電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In an atom, an electron
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.30,0:34:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,並不存在於軌道之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}doesn't exist between orbitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.04,0:34:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它從一個軌道消失\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It disappears from one orbital
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.84,0:34:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,又在另一個軌道出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and reappears in another.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.51,0:34:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你坐電梯從2樓去4樓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's as if you took an elevator from the second floor to the fourth floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.34,0:34:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,卻憑空消失\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but ceased to exist in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.65,0:34:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,還有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And another thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.38,0:34:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,量子電梯並不會停在特定的樓層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Quantum elevators only stop at certain floors.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.35,0:34:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,電子的軌道尺寸有著嚴格的限制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sizes of the electron orbits are strictly limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.79,0:34:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,每種元素的原子都不相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and different for the atoms of every element.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.16,0:34:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是元素各不相同的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why the elements are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.53,0:34:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,所有物質的化學屬性都由它的電子的軌道決定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The chemistry of anything is determined by its electron orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.50,0:34:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,將電子束縛在軌道上的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The force that holds an electron in orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.40,0:34:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,和重力沒有絲毫關係\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has nothing to do with gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.24,0:34:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,它是電氣引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a force of electrical attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.81,0:34:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,電子沿著波浪形的圓環\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The electron dances a wavy ring
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.14,0:35:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,環繞氫原子的原子核運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}around the central nucleus of a hydrogen atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.81,0:35:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,從一個軌道跳到另一個軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And makes quantum leaps from orbit to orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.85,0:35:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,忽上忽下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Up or down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.16,0:35:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,軌道越大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The larger the orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.56,0:35:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,電子的能量越大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the greater the energy of an electron.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.63,0:35:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,電子必須獲取能量才能跳躍到更大的軌道上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An electron has to get energy to leap to a larger orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.20,0:35:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,然後必須釋放能量才能跳回來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it has to lose energy to jump back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.03,0:35:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,每次向上的跳躍都是原子吸收光波的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every upward leap is caused by... an atom absorbing a light wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.81,0:35:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我們還不知道是什麼使它向下跳躍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But we have no idea what causes the downward leaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.64,0:35:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我們只知道向下跳躍產生光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What we do know that such leaps always produce a light wave
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.25,0:35:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這種光波的顏色與軌道間的能量差異相吻合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}whose color matches the energy difference between the orbitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽的表面輻射出所有顏色的光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun's surface radiates light waves of all colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.03,0:35:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你透過棱鏡看日光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you look at sunlight through a prism,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.86,0:35:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你能看到它的光譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you'll see its spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.50,0:35:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,當你用望遠鏡放大光譜時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When you magnify the spectrum with a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.37,0:35:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,就像約瑟夫·夫瑯和費那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as Joseph Fraunhofer did,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.27,0:35:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你就可以窺視\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you raise the curtain
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.87,0:36:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,電子在原子中跳躍的真相\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the electron dance within the atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.11,0:36:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,當電子的能量衰弱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the energy of the electron flags,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.35,0:36:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,它降到較低的軌道時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and it drops to a lower orbital,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.05,0:36:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,光波逸散\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the light wave it emits scatters.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.45,0:36:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,大多數不會到我們這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of it doesn't reach us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.89,0:36:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,這就留下了一個黑暗的空當\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That leaves a dark gap
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.45,0:36:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,或者說 光譜中的黑色豎線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or black vertical line in the spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.39,0:36:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,這些黑線就是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These dark lines are the shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.96,0:36:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,氫原子在太陽大氣層中造成的陰影\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}cast by hydrogen atoms in the atmosphere of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.56,0:36:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,鈉原子發出不同的陰影\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sodium atoms cast different shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.30,0:36:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的電子按照不同的曲子跳舞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their electrons dance to a different tune.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.40,0:36:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,一粒鹽由鈉原子和氯原子組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A grain of table salt is composed of sodium and chlorine atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.14,0:36:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,千萬億的原子瘋狂地舞動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ten million billion of them doing their crazy dances
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.61,0:36:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,僅僅是在一粒鹽中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a single grain of salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.48,0:36:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,一個鐵原子有26個電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And a single iron atom with 26 electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.42,0:36:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,龐大的宛如百老匯音樂劇的製作團隊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is like a great big production number in a Broadway musical.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.49,0:36:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,當你用分光儀觀察星星時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When you look at a star with a spectroscope,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.43,0:36:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,在它大氣層中所有元素上都能看到黑線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you see the dark lines from all the elements in its atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.57,0:36:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,給我任意一個物體的光譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Show me the spectrum of anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.47,0:37:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不論是在地球上的 還是在遙遠的星星上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}whether here on Earth or from a distant star,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.27,0:37:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我都可以告訴你 它的元素構成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and I'll tell you what it's made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.34,0:37:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,夫瑯和費線是元素的原子簽名\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fraunhofer's lines are the atomic signatures
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.98,0:37:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,遍佈整個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the elements writ large across the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.98,0:37:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,如同科學歷史上的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As with every other major revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.08,0:37:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,其他重大發現一樣  它帶來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the history of science, it opened the way
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.62,0:37:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,更新更深層次的謎團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to newer and deeper mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.62,0:37:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,還有更多地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And to the revelation that there were
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.62,0:37:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,秘密依然藏在光線中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}many more secrets hiding in the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.59,0:37:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,當夫瑯和費把望遠鏡和棱鏡結合在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Joseph Fraunhofer combined a prism with a telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.53,0:37:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,用它們探索天空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and turned it toward the skies,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.80,0:37:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他將星星與我們之間的距離縮短了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he brought the stars much closer to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.28,0:38:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他39歲時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When he was only 39,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.01,0:38:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他身患重病\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he contracted a fatal illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.18,0:38:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是由於早年長期曝露在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Perhaps as a result of his early and long-term exposure
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.85,0:38:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,製作玻璃的有毒化學物質的緣故\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the toxic chemicals of glassmaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.79,0:38:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你永遠不知道下一個天才在何處誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You never know where the next genius will come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.73,0:38:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道我們錯過了多少天才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How many of them do we leave in the rubble?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.23,0:38:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,對一位孤兒的善行給王子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The prince and his kingdom were immeasurably enriched
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.50,0:38:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,和他的王國帶來不可計量的財富\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by that act of kindness to a poor orphan.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.87,0:38:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,夫瑯和費的發現將巴伐利亞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fraunhofer's discoveries transformed Bavaria
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.31,0:38:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,從偏僻的鄉下變成高科技的製造中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from a rural backwater to a technological powerhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.41,0:38:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在他彌留之際  政府急切地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As he lay dying, the government was desperate
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.85,0:38:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,想要保留他所有的關於\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to preserve every shred of his precious knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.75,0:38:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,高科技光學玻璃的寶貴知識\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about the high technology of optical glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.09,0:38:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,但這只能讓一個人知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it could only be divulged to a person
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.03,0:38:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,此人有著最高級別的涉密權限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with top security clearance--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.23,0:38:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,鑄幣局主管\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the director of the mint.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.08,0:39:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,政府保留了夫瑯和費的技術\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The government kept Fraunhofer's technology
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.68,0:39:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,用於製造完美的光學玻璃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for making perfect optical glass
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.59,0:39:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,一個上百年的國家機密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a State secret for another hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.86,0:39:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,後來證明這給某人帶來很大的阻礙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This would prove to be a major obstacle
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.89,0:39:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,以後我們會提到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for someone we'll meet later in our journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.39,0:39:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,但夫瑯和費不能容忍這樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Fraunhofer would allow no such secrecy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.96,0:39:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,對他的科學研究保密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where his pure scientific research was concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.56,0:39:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他知道科學需要開放才能昌盛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He knew that science requires openness to flourish;
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.20,0:39:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我們對於自然地瞭解屬於全世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that our understanding of nature belongs to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.27,0:39:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,夫瑯和費發現譜線後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As soon as Fraunhofer discovered the spectral lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.21,0:39:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他立即發表了所有的成果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he published everything he knew about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.78,0:39:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,如此重要的發現帶來的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the reverberations of his momentous discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.61,0:39:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,持續至今\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}echo still.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.55,0:39:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,他的譜線揭示了可觀測宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His spectral lines revealed that the visible cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.56,0:39:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,是由相同的元素構成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is all made of the same elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.86,0:40:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,行星們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.47,0:40:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.31,0:40:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,星系們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.69,0:40:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我們  還有所有的生命體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We, ourselves, and all of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.36,0:40:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,擁有共同的物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The same star stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.34,0:40:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他讓我們知道了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He made it possible for us to know
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.04,0:40:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,其他星球的大氣層中有些什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what's in the atmosphere of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.98,0:40:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,遠在上百萬光年外的星系中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And in galaxies millions of light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.65,0:40:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,譜線不止揭示了遙遠物體的成分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Spectral lines revealed not only the composition
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.68,0:41:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,也揭示了他們是在靠近還是遠離我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of far-off objects, but also their motion towards or away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.39,0:41:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,通過它 我們發現我們的宇宙還在擴張\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Using them, we discovered that our universe is expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.49,0:41:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但分光儀最偉大的作用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But perhaps the greatest revelation of spectroscopy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.10,0:41:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是發現了不可見光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is the discovery of the thing it cannot see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.91,0:41:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,暗物質的隱蔽宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A hidden universe of dark matter
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.11,0:41:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,質量比我們熟悉的宇宙超出6倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}six times more massive than the familiar cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.38,0:41:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,由某些神秘的物質組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's made of some mysterious substance
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.58,0:41:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,不會發出 反射或者吸收任何形式的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that does not emit, reflect or absorb any kind of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.18,0:41:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它的引力我們才知道它的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We only know it's there because of its gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.69,0:41:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,它的引力吸引著星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which pulls on all the galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.79,0:41:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,並為其中的恆星加速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and speeds up the visible stars within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.53,0:41:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的眼睛可以看見很多種類的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are many more kinds of light than our eyes can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.03,0:41:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,認為我們的自然只有可見光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Confining our perception of nature to visible light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.47,0:41:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同聽的音樂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is like listening to music
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.80,0:41:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一個八度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in only one octave.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.94,0:41:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,其實還有很多很多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are so many more.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.98,0:41:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他們僅僅是波長的區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They differ only in wavelength,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.95,0:42:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,只是範圍很大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but over a huge range.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.08,0:42:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,比如 紅外線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For instance, infrared light...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.99,0:42:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,威廉費歇爾發現的那種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the kind that William Herschel discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.16,0:42:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,X光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or X-ray light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.00,0:42:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,無線電波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or radio light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.81,0:42:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,伽馬射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or in gamma-ray light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.45,0:42:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,不僅是看東西的方式不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These are not just different ways of seeing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.75,0:42:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,不同的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These other kinds of light
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.35,0:42:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,揭示出宇宙中不同的物體和現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}reveal different objects and phenomena in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.99,0:42:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,比方說通過伽馬射線 它使我們可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In gamma-ray light, for example, we can see mysterious explosions
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.19,0:42:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,不再錯過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in distant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.96,0:42:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,遙遠星系的神秘爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we would otherwise miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.20,0:42:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,通過微波 我們可以看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And in microwave light, we can see all the way back
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.10,0:42:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙誕生之初的情景\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the birth of the universe.
